"title": "5281: crucifixion",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5281: crucifixion",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A most painful, cruel and protracted form of execution which involved the victim being roped or nailed to an elevated wooden cross. This form of execution was favoured by the Romans, who regarded it as a deterrent to political rebellion against the authority of Rome at the time of Jesus Christ.</p>\n<h2>The method of crucifixion</h2>\n<h3>The victim was scourged before crucifixion</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:1\">JHN 19:1</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:26\">MAT 27:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:15\">MRK 15:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:22\">LUK 23:22</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:16\">LUK 23:16</a></p>\n<h3>The victim carried his cross</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:17\">JHN 19:17</a></strong> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:32-Matt27:33\">MAT 27:32–27:33</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:21-Mark15:22\">MRK 15:21–15:22</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:26\">LUK 23:26</a></p>\n<h3>The victim was fixed to the cross</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:33\">LUK 23:33</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:35\">MAT 27:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:24\">MRK 15:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:23\">JHN 19:23</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:25\">JHN 20:25</a></p>\n<h3>A charge board was fixed to the cross</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:37\">MAT 27:37</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:26\">MRK 15:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:38\">LUK 23:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:19\">JHN 19:19</a></p>\n<h3>The victim's sufferings were protracted</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:54\">MAT 27:54</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:39\">MRK 15:39</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:47\">LUK 23:47</a><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:32-John19:33\">JHN 19:32–19:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:34\">JHN 19:34</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:25\">MRK 15:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:33\">MRK 15:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:37\">MRK 15:37</a></p>\n<h2>OT prophecies concerning Jesus Christ's crucifixion</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps22:16-Ps22:18\">PSA 22:16–22:18</a></strong> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod12:46\">EXO 12:46</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num9:12\">NUM 9:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps34:20\">PSA 34:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:36\">JHN 19:36</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps22:1\">PSA 22:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps22:7-Ps22:8\">PSA 22:7–22:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps69:21\">PSA 69:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps109:25\">PSA 109:25</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa50:6\">ISA 50:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa53:5\">ISA 53:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa53:9\">ISA 53:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos8:9-Amos8:10\">AMO 8:9–8:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech12:10\">ZEC 12:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech13:6-Zech13:7\">ZEC 13:6–13:7</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ's predictions concerning the manner of his death</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:32-John12:33\">JHN 12:32–12:33</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:14\">JHN 3:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:28\">JHN 8:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John18:31-John18:32\">JHN 18:31–18:32</a></p>\n<h2>Responsibility for the crucifixion ascribed to Jews and Gentiles alike</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor2:8\">1CO 2:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:15\">JHN 19:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:23\">ACT 2:23</a></p>\n<h2>The crucifixion involved a curse</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut21:22-Deut21:23\">DEU 21:22–21:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:17\">GEN 2:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:30\">ACT 5:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:39\">ACT 10:39</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:29\">ACT 13:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:13\">GAL 3:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:24\">1PE 2:24</a></p>\n<h2>The crucifixion involved shame</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:2\">HEB 12:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:23\">1CO 1:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:8\">PHP 2:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:13\">HEB 13:13</a></p>\n<h2>Believers are united with Jesus Christ in his crucifixion</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal2:20\">GAL 2:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:6\">ROM 6:6</a></p>\n<h2>Crucifixion illustrates discipleship</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:34\">MRK 8:34</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:24\">MAT 16:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:23\">LUK 9:23</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:38\">MAT 10:38</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke14:27\">LUK 14:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:24\">GAL 5:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal6:14\">GAL 6:14</a></p>\n<h2>The crucifixion is remembered in glory</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev5:6\">REV 5:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:7\">REV 1:7</a></p>",
